Read and apply wow/task/RULES.md first.

The active program item filepath is given in the user prompt. Read it first.

Synchronize child workstream state into the parent program plan.

- Discover child plans by matching `Program:` in `## Orchestration Metadata`
  to the provided parent path
- For each child, read:
  - current phase/progress from `## Execution Plan`
  - latest blockers from `## Progress Checkpoint` (if present)
  - pending dependencies from `Depends-On`
- Update parent `## Workstreams` status fields with:
  - state (`not-started`, `in-progress`, `blocked`, `ready-for-merge`, `done`)
  - blocker summary
  - next owner action
- Add/replace parent `## Sync Snapshot` with:
  - timestamp
  - completed items this sync
  - blocked items and reason
  - ready-to-converge candidates
- Do not move files between workflow states
- Report: parent path + sync timestamp + blocker table
